            <fr:title text="Holomorphic function">Holomorphic function</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A holomorphic function defined on an open set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \subseteq  \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> is a complex-valued function that is complex differentiable at every point. In other words, the limit
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[f'(z) = \lim _{h \to  0} \frac {f(z + h) - f(z)}{h}]]></fr:tex>
  exists for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z \in  U]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
